page.title: 06FRINTON ON SEA 06200219
page.content: {FRINTON ON SEA}is a small seaside town in North-East Essex. It caters for both local residents and holiday makers,many of whom come with their families. Frinton also has a high proportion of elderly and wealthy residents and the shopping facilities reflect this. Frinton developed after 1886 when the railway atation was built. Before this time there were few houses for a population of thirty. Some of the older village has disappeared into the sea, as coastal erosion has been significant in the area. The level crossing gates form a barrier between Frinton and the outside world and {'the Gates'}are word-famous. To a certain extent they preserve the 'exclusive' nature of Frinton.Houses inside 'the Gates' fetch a higher price than outside.
